{"book":"1 Corinthians","chapter":15,"questions":[{"id":"1cor-15-q1","type":"multiple_choice","question":"What is the main topic of this chapter?","options":["Church discipline","Spiritual gifts","The resurrection of the dead","Marriage and divorce"],"answer":"The resurrection of the dead","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 15:12"},{"id":"1cor-15-q2","type":"multiple_choice","question":"Paul says if Christ has not been raised, then what?","options":["The law still applies","Their faith is in vain","They must try harder","The church should disband"],"answer":"Their faith is in vain","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 15:14"},{"id":"1cor-15-q3","type":"true_false","question":"Paul says the resurrection body is the same as the natural body.","answer":"false","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 15:42-44"},{"id":"1cor-15-q4","type":"fill_blank","question":"O death, where is your victory? O death, where is your _____?","answer":"sting","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 15:55"},{"id":"1cor-15-q5","type":"fill_blank","question":"The last _____ that will be abolished is death.","answer":"enemy","verse_reference":"1 Corinthians 15:26"}]}
